  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA188-kiḷavi">itu pakaṟkuṟi maṟuttu varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how marriage is asked for by refusing the daytime tryst.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA188">
<l>            paṭunīrc cilampiṟ kalitta vāḻaik</l>
<l>            koṭumaṭa līṉṟa kūrvāyk kuvimukai</l>
<l>            yoḷḷiḻai makaḷi rilaṅkuvaḷait toṭūu</l>
<l>            melviraṉ mōcai pōlak kāntaḷ</l>
<l>            vaḷḷitaḻ tōyum vāṉṟōy veṟpa </l>
<l>            naṉṟi viḷaivun tītoṭu varumeṉa</l>
<l>            vaṉṟunaṟ kaṟintaṉa ḷāyiṟ kuṉṟattut</l>
<l>            tēmutir cilampiṟ ṟaṭaiiya</l>
<l>            vēymaruḷ paṇaittō ḷaḻiyalaṇ maṉṉē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>O man from the sky-touching mountain,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the piled buds with sharp edges brought forth by the bent</l>
<l rend="indent2">stem of the plantain, swollen on the water-rich mountain side,</l>
<l rend="indent">touches the many petals of the Malabar-lily,</l>
<l rend="indent2">as the ornament on the soft fingers</l>
<l rend="indent2">joins with the shining bangles of bright-jewelled women,</l>
<l rend="indent2">– if she had understood well that day</l>
<l rend="indent2">that as the result of kindness too something evil arises,</l>
<l>she would not be desolate indeed,</l>
<l rend="indent3">bamboo shoulder resembling bamboo,</l>
<l rend="indent4">plump on the honey-ripening slopes up the hill.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
